<sect1><title>Implementation Details</title>
  <sect2><title>Code Organization</title>
    <para>
      <programlisting>
        <![CDATA[
      .
      |-- bin
      |-- debian
      |-- doc
      |-- etc
      |-- lib
      |   `-- ODA
      |-- scripts
      `-- testing
      ]]>
      </programlisting>
    </para>
    <para>
      The <emphasis>Database.pm</emphasis> Perl module provides the API for
      developers in order to interact with the OSCAR Database.
    </para>
  </sect2>
  <sect2><title>Testing</title>
    <para>
      Selector source code provides testing mechanisms, actually unit tests,
      that aims to provide basic testing capabilities for specific Selector
      features. All the tests are in the <emphasis>testing</emphasis>, one can
      execute them individually.
    </para>
  </sect2>
